      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but instrumenting everything might be too heavy for the CPU on this chip. I'm worried about the overhead of logging everything if the system is already struggling.\n\nIs there any way to identify if these leaks are coming from third-party libraries or some obscure kernel-level driver? It feels so random, like these tiny bits of memory are just being snatched away by something we can't even see. How do I narrow down those \"hidden\" sources without killing my performance?",
